members.name: showZoomButtons
members.description: States whether the zoom in / zoom out / home buttons should be shown in the Graphics View or not. Default: false

members.name: showFullscreenButton
members.description: Whether fullscreen button should be visible

members.name: ggbStyles
members.description: Custom CSS styles to apply to the GeoGebra applet.

members.name: width
members.description: Applet width

members.name: height
members.description: Applet height

members.name: src
members.description: Source of the GeoGebra file to load (base64-encoded string, material ID prefixed with "ggbid:", or file URL)

members.name: hideMenus
members.description: Hide toolbar and menus. Note that this does not prevent editing. TODO: remove

members.name: borderColor
members.description: Color of the border line drawn around the applet panel (as hex rgb string). Default: gray

members.name: borderRadius
members.description: Size of applet's border radius in pixels.

members.name: enableRightClick
members.description: States whether right clicks should be handled by the applet. Setting this parameter to "false" disables context menus, properties dialogs and right-click-zooming. Default: true. NB also enables/disables some keyboard shortcuts eg Delete and Ctrl + R (recompute all objects). Default: true

members.name: enableLabelDrags
members.description: States whether labels can be dragged. Default: true

members.name: enableShiftDragZoom
members.description: States whether the Graphics View(s) should be moveable using Shift mouse drag (or. Ctrl + mouse drag) or zoomable using Shift + mouse wheel (or Ctrl + mouse wheel). Setting this parameter to "false" disables moving and zooming of the drawing pad. Default: true

members.name: errorDialogsActive
members.description: States whether error dialogs will be shown if an invalid input is entered (using the Input Bar or JavaScript) Default: true

members.name: showMenuBar
members.description: States whether the menubar of GeoGebra should be shown in the applet. Default: false

members.name: showToolBar
members.description: States whether the toolbar with the construction mode buttons should be shown in the applet. Default: false

members.name: showToolBarHelp
members.description: States whether the toolbar help text right to the toolbar buttons should be shown in the applet

members.name: customToolBar
members.description: Sets the toolbar according to a custom toolbar string where the int values are Toolbar Mode Values, `,` adds a separator within a menu, `|` starts a new menu and `||` adds a separator in the toolbar before starting a new menu. This will override the saved toolbar from the .ggb file / base64 string. Custom tools are numbered 100 001, 100 002, etc

members.name: showAlgebraInput
members.description: States whether the algebra input line (with input field, greek letters and command list) should be shown in the applet. Default: false

members.name: showResetIcon
members.description: States whether a small icon (GeoGebra ellipse) should be shown in the upper right corner of the applet. Clicking on this icon resets the applet (i.e. it reloads the file given in the filename parameter). Default: false

members.name: language
members.description: ISO language string. GeoGebra tries to set your local language automatically (if it is available among the supported languages, of course). The default language for unsupported languages is English. If you want to specify a certain language manually, please use this parameter.

members.name: country
members.description: ISO country string. This parameter only makes sense if you use it together with the language parameter.

members.name: appletId
members.description: This parameter allows you to specify the argument passed to the JavaScript function ggbOnInit(), which is called once the applet is fully initialised. This is useful when you have multiple applets on a page.

members.name: allowStyleBar
members.description: Determines whether the Style Bar can be shown (or will be shown if just Graphics View 1 is showing). Default: false

members.name: randomize
members.description: Determines whether random numbers should be randomized on file load. Useful when you want the app to reload in exactly the same state it was saved. Default: true

members.name: randomSeed
members.description: Specify seed for random numbers. Note that if you save a state of the app after user interacted with it and try to reload that state with the same randomSeed, you may get a different result. Use randomize for those use-cases.

members.name: useBrowserForJs
members.description: When true, GeoGebra: runs ggbOnInit from HTML, ignores ggbOnInit from file, and ignores JS update scripts of objects in file. When false, GeoGebra: ignores ggbOnInit from HTML (use appletOnLoad parameter of GGBApplet instead), runs ggbOnInit from file, and runs JS update scripts of objects in file. Default: false

members.name: showLogging
members.description: Determines whether logging is shown in the Browser's console. Default: false

members.name: capturingThreshold
members.description: Determines the sensitivity of object selection. The default value of 3 is usually fine to select and drag objects both with the mouse and touch. Use larger values (e.g. 4 or 5) to make it easier to select and drag objects. Default: 3

members.name: enableFileFeatures
members.description: Determines whether file saving, file loading, sign in and Options > Save settings are enabled. This argument is ignored when menubar is not showing. Default: true

members.name: enableUndoRedo
members.description: Determines whether Undo and Redo icons are shown. This argument is ignored when toolbar is not showing. Default: true

members.name: perspective
members.description: For values see SetPerspective_Command in the GeoGebra Manual. Just for a blank start ie shouldn't be used with material_id, filename or ggbBase64 parameters

members.name: enable3d
members.description: Whether 3D should be enabled (for exam mode).

members.name: enableCAS
members.description: Whether CAS should be enabled (for exam mode).

members.name: algebraInputPosition
members.description: Determines whether input bar should be shown in algebra, on top of the applet or under the applet. When left empty (default), the position depends on file.

members.name: preventFocus
members.description: When set to true, this prevents the applet from getting focus automatically at the start. Default: false

members.name: scaleContainerClass
members.description: Name of CSS class that is used as container; applet will scale to fit into the container.

members.name: autoHeight
members.description: `true` to restrict the width of the applet and compute height automatically, add autoHeight: true. `false` if you want the applet to be restricted by both width and height of the container

members.name: allowUpscale
members.description: Determines whether automatic scaling may scale the applet up. Default: false

members.name: playButton
members.description: Determines whether a preview image and a play button should be rendered in place of the applet. Pushing the play button initializes the applet. Default: false

members.name: scale
members.description: Ratio by which the applet should be scaled (eg. 2 makes the applet 2 times bigger, including all texts and UI elements). Default: 1

members.name: showAnimationButton
members.description: Whether animation button should be visible

members.name: showSuggestionButtons
members.description: Whether suggestion buttons (special points, solve) in Algebra View should be visible

members.name: showStartTooltip
members.description: Whether "Welcome" tooltip should be shown

members.name: rounding
members.description: String composed of number of decimal places and flags — valid flags are "s" for significant digits and "r" for rational numbers. Hence "10" means 10 decimal places, "10s" stands for 10 significant digits.

members.name: buttonShadows
members.description: Whether buttons should have shadow

members.name: buttonRounding
members.description: Relative radius of button's rounded border. The border radius in pixels is buttonRounding * height /2, where height is the height of the button. Default: 0.2

members.name: buttonBorderColor
members.description: Border color of buttons on the graphics view. Default is black, if the button background is white, otherwise one shade darker than the background color

members.name: editorBackgroundColor
members.description: Background color of the evaluator app

members.name: editorForegroundColor
members.description: Foreground (text) color of the equation editor (appname = "evaluator")

members.name: textmode
members.description: Whether editor is in text mode or not (appname = "evaluator"). Default: false

members.name: showKeyboardOnFocus
members.description: Whether to show keyboard when input is focused. When set to true, keyboard is always shown, for false it never appears, for auto it's shown unless closed by user. Default: true in evaluator app, auto in other apps

members.name: keyboardType
members.description: Which keyboard is shown for equation editor (appname = "evaluator")

members.name: transparentGraphics
members.description: Whether the Graphics View and Graphics View 2 should be transparent

members.name: disabledJavaScript
members.description: Whether running JavaScript from material files is disabled or not.

members.name: detachedKeyboardParent
members.description: When set, the keyboard should be attached to the first element in DOM that fits the selector.

members.name: resetKey
members.description: Used to force reset of the applet. Increment this property to reset the applet.

attributes.name: showAlgebraInput
attributes.description: States whether the algebra input line (with input field, greek letters and command list) should be shown in the applet. Default: false

attributes.name: showResetIcon
attributes.description: States whether a small icon (GeoGebra ellipse) should be shown in the upper right corner of the applet. Clicking on this icon resets the applet (i.e. it reloads the file given in the filename parameter). Default: false

attributes.name: language
attributes.description: ISO language string. GeoGebra tries to set your local language automatically (if it is available among the supported languages, of course). The default language for unsupported languages is English. If you want to specify a certain language manually, please use this parameter.

attributes.name: country
attributes.description: ISO country string. This parameter only makes sense if you use it together with the language parameter.

attributes.name: appletId
attributes.description: This parameter allows you to specify the argument passed to the JavaScript function ggbOnInit(), which is called once the applet is fully initialised. This is useful when you have multiple applets on a page.

attributes.name: allowStyleBar
attributes.description: Determines whether the Style Bar can be shown (or will be shown if just Graphics View 1 is showing). Default: false

attributes.name: randomize
attributes.description: Determines whether random numbers should be randomized on file load. Useful when you want the app to reload in exactly the same state it was saved. Default: true

attributes.name: randomSeed
attributes.description: Specify seed for random numbers. Note that if you save a state of the app after user interacted with it and try to reload that state with the same randomSeed, you may get a different result. Use randomize for those use-cases.

attributes.name: useBrowserForJs
attributes.description: When true, GeoGebra: runs ggbOnInit from HTML, ignores ggbOnInit from file, and ignores JS update scripts of objects in file. attributes.name: showLogging
attributes.description: Determines whether logging is shown in the Browser's console. Default: false

attributes.name: capturingThreshold
attributes.description: Determines the sensitivity of object selection. The default value of 3 is usually fine to select and drag objects both with the mouse and touch. Use larger values (e.g. 4 or 5) to make it easier to select and drag objects. Default: 3

attributes.name: enableFileFeatures
attributes.description: Determines whether file saving, file loading, sign in and Options > Save settings are enabled. This argument is ignored when menubar is not showing. Default: true

attributes.name: enableUndoRedo
attributes.description: Determines whether Undo and Redo icons are shown. This argument is ignored when toolbar is not showing. Default: true

attributes.name: perspective
attributes.description: For values see SetPerspective_Command in the GeoGebra Manual. Just for a blank start ie shouldn't be used with material_id, filename or ggbBase64 parameters

attributes.name: enable3d
attributes.description: Whether 3D should be enabled (for exam mode).

attributes.name: enableCAS
attributes.description: Whether CAS should be enabled (for exam mode).

attributes.name: algebraInputPosition
attributes.description: Determines whether input bar should be shown in algebra, on top of the applet or under the applet. When left empty (default), the position depends on file.

attributes.name: preventFocus
attributes.description: When set to true, this prevents the applet from getting focus automatically at the start. Default: false

attributes.name: scaleContainerClass
attributes.description: Name of CSS class that is used as container; applet will scale to fit into the container.

attributes.name: autoHeight
attributes.description: `true` to restrict the width of the applet and compute height automatically, add autoHeight: true. `false` if you want the applet to be restricted by both width and height of the container

attributes.name: allowUpscale
attributes.description: Determines whether automatic scaling may scale the applet up. Default: false

attributes.name: scale

attributes.name: showAnimationButton
attributes.description: Whether animation button should be visible

attributes.name: showFullscreenButton
attributes.description: Whether fullscreen button should be visible

attributes.name: showSuggestionButtons
attributes.description: Whether suggestion buttons (special points, solve) in Algebra View should be visible

attributes.name: showStartTooltip
attributes.description: Whether "Welcome" tooltip should be shown

attributes.name: rounding
attributes.description: String composed of number of decimal places and flags — valid flags are "s" for significant digits and "r" for rational numbers. Hence "10" means 10 decimal places, "10s" stands for 10 significant digits.

attributes.name: buttonShadows
attributes.description: Whether buttons should have shadow

attributes.name: buttonRounding

attributes.name: buttonBorderColor

attributes.name: editorBackgroundColor
attributes.description: Background color of the evaluator app

attributes.name: editorForegroundColor
attributes.description: Foreground (text) color of the equation editor (appname = "evaluator")

attributes.name: textmode
attributes.description: Whether editor is in text mode or not (appname = "evaluator"). Default: false

attributes.name: keyboardType

attributes.name: transparentGraphics

attributes.name: disabledJavaScript
attributes.description: Whether running JavaScript from material files is disabled or not.

attributes.name: detachedKeyboardParent
attributes.description: When set, the keyboard should be attached to the first element in DOM that fits the selector.

members.name: showToolBarHelp
members.description: States whether the toolbar help text right to the toolbar buttons should be shown in the applet

members.name: customToolBar
members.description: Sets the toolbar according to a custom toolbar string where the int values are Toolbar Mode Values, `,` adds a separator within a menu, `|` starts a new menu and `||` adds a separator in the toolbar before starting a new menu. This will override the saved toolbar from the .ggb file / base64 string. Custom tools are numbered 100 001, 100 002, etc

members.name: showResetIcon
members.description: States whether a small icon (GeoGebra ellipse) should be shown in the upper right corner of the applet. Clicking on this icon resets the applet (i.e. it reloads the file given in the filename parameter). Default: false

members.name: language
members.description: ISO language string. GeoGebra tries to set your local language automatically (if it is available among the supported languages, of course). The default language for unsupported languages is English. If you want to specify a certain language manually, please use this parameter.

members.name: country
members.description: ISO country string. This parameter only makes sense if you use it together with the language parameter.

members.name: appletId
members.description: This parameter allows you to specify the argument passed to the JavaScript function ggbOnInit(), which is called once the applet is fully initialised. This is useful when you have multiple applets on a page.

members.name: allowStyleBar
members.description: Determines whether the Style Bar can be shown (or will be shown if just Graphics View 1 is showing). Default: false

members.name: randomize
members.description: Determines whether random numbers should be randomized on file load. Useful when you want the app to reload in exactly the same state it was saved. Default: true

members.name: randomSeed
members.description: Specify seed for random numbers. Note that if you save a state of the app after user interacted with it and try to reload that state with the same randomSeed, you may get a different result. Use randomize for those use-cases.

members.name: useBrowserForJs
members.description: When true, GeoGebra: runs ggbOnInit from HTML, ignores ggbOnInit from file, and ignores JS update scripts of objects in file. members.name: showLogging

members.name: capturingThreshold
members.description: Determines the sensitivity of object selection. The default value of 3 is usually fine to select and drag objects both with the mouse and touch. Use larger values (e.g. 4 or 5) to make it easier to select and drag objects. Default: 3
